.TH "batadv_bla_check_claim" 9 "batadv_bla_check_claim" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
batadv_bla_check_claim \- check if address is claimed
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "bool" batadv_bla_check_claim
.BI "(struct batadv_priv *bat_priv "  ","
.BI "u8 *addr "  ","
.BI "unsigned short vid "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "bat_priv" 12
the bat priv with all the soft interface information
.IP "addr" 12
mac address of which the claim status is checked
.IP "vid" 12
the VLAN ID
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
addr is checked if this address is claimed by the local device itself.
.SH "RETURN"
true if bla is disabled or the mac is claimed by the device,
false if the device addr is already claimed by another gateway
